    "recap_headline": "Washington State University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "PULLMAN, Wash. (March 20, 2026)\n\u2013\nNick Lewis\nfired six innings and Washington State matched a season-high with 14 hits in a 7-3 victory over Grand Canyon at Bailey-Brayton Field Friday.\nFive Cougars (8-12, 2-2 Mountain West) recorded multiple-hit games led by\nRyan Skjonsby's\nthree-hit game while\nMatt Priest\nhit a two-run homer to back Lewis who struck out five and allowed just three runs in six innings.\nAugust Richie\nstruck out three in three scoreless innings of relief to earn the save.\nPriest gave WSU a 2-0 lead with a two-run home run in the third inning and the Cougars scored in the next three innings Richie worked the final three innings to close out the home-opening win.\nWSU played at home for the first time this season after playing the first 19 games on the road.\nKEY MOMENTS OF THE GAME\nPriest hit a long two-run home run to left field in the third inning for his first career homer. WSU scored twice more in the fourth highlighted by\nKyler Northrop's\nRBI-double to left field. Skjonsby drove in\nMason Pirello\nin the fifth inning before\nDustin Robinson\nand\nOllie Obenour\ns connected on back-to-back RBI-doubles off the right field wall in the sixth inning.\nLewis allowed just a sacrifice fly in the fourth inning and a two-run home run in the sixth inning.\nINSIDE THE BOX SCORE\nMax Hartman\ntripled off the centerfield wall in the 1\nst\nfor his 4\nth\ntriple of the season\nGavin Roy\ndoubled to right-centerfield in the 3\nrd\nto extend his hitting streak to 7 games\nMatt Priest\nhit his 1\nst\ncareer home run in the 4\nth\ninning, extending his on-base streak to 6 games\nNick Lewis\nimproved to 2-1, has worked 5+ innings in last 5 starts\n8 Cougars recorded hits, Roy, Obenour, Robinson, Skjonsby and Northrop each had multiple-hits\nSkjonsby matched a career-high with 3 hits\nON DEC\nK\nThe series continues Saturday at 2:05 p.m.",
